task:
Review this JavaScript pagination helper for an API client. It fetches all pages by following a 'nextCursor' field:

async function fetchAll(client, path) {
  let results = [];
  let cursor = null;
  do {
    const res = await client.get(path, { cursor });
    results = results.concat(res.items);
    cursor = res.nextCursor;
  } while (cursor);
  return results;
}

The API can return up to millions of items and occasionally returns a transient 503.
